  "text": "F(1,58) = 5.89, p = .018; Figure 4A ]. In the ZnT3 KO mice, stress enhanced fear memory, as indicated by increased freezing time during the cue presentation (p = .004, Bonferronicorrected). In the WT mice, stress had no significant effect (p = .752). However, it also appeared that control ZnT3 KO mice showed weaker fear memory than control WT mice, as was previously reported by [CITATION_1] . Therefore, we also directly compared the control groups, and confirmed that ZnT3 KO mice froze less than WT mice during cue presentation [t-test: t(28) = 2.16, p = .040], indicating weaker cued fear memory.",
